03/08/2010
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Police shut down four popular torrent websites on Monday (August 2nd) in the country's biggest action so far against internet piracy.
The file-sharing sites -- nanoset.net, rapidadd.com, 4storing.com and afasta.com -- have been accused of illegally distributing books, games, music, software and films.
According to the police, the websites were run by organised crime networks.
(AFP, Novinar - 02/08/10;
BNT, 24 Chasa - 01/08/10)
